title: Mission Manager
description: Operates/manages highly sophisticated, multi-million, multi-component computer based collection systems in the execution of National Intelligence Requirements. Configures SIGINT (DNR/DNI) system tasking, normalization, survey, equipment configuration, basic signal analysis, interpretation of system health parameters and routing process ensuring appropriate threads are monitored so that data is forwarded in a timely manner. First hand experience operation GOTS processing tools, and COTS tools including TRIREME, CircuitRaptor, PacketRaptor and BladeRunner. Understanding of SDH/OTN/Carrier Grade Ethernet and modern telecommunications networks, packet and circuit switched. Provide value assessment on collection and reporting trends. Derive Network knowledge of the collection environment to meet customer’s strategic and mission prioritized needs. Define system requirements developing technical solutions, functional analysis, conduct trade studies and perform test and evaluation activities. Partner with system engineers to design, integrate and deploy additional system capabilities to further the system’s mission performance. Develop strategies and recommendations for optimization of collection. Troubleshoot signal and data-flow issues related to SIGINT systems. Teams with technical personnel to resolve all systems issues in an immediate manner. Partners daily with analytic and technical team members to share information, align resources, and provide optimum support to customers and program organizations. Interact daily with program management and engineering divisions pertaining to system health and performance. Compiles procedural and statistical information regarding system performance as required. Maintains cognizance of system architecture, ensuring integrity through all software and system upgrades. Provides 24/7 call-in support to maintain system health and perform ad hoc urgent tasking as required. • Recipient - National Intelligence Meritorious Unit Citation
name: James Groff

title: Lead Technical Trainer
description: Lead platform instructor for mission critical SSO. Authored and delivered, 8 hour in-depth tasking and validation training course for newly developed DOD multi-site system. Revised out-dated training materials to include: student guides, slide presentations and practical exercises for several national level training courses. Handpicked among peers to work directly with system engineers to train and develop highly compartmented real-time analytical tool. • Selected by management and customer for transition to Mission Management
name: James Groff

title: New Homes Community Sales Manager
description: Achieve and exceed sales in accordance with monthly performance goals of the community plan. Coordinated all aspects of new home sales from marketing, sales contract, construction to settlement. Ensured sales site operated to State and local code including all Federal Fair Housing Policies. Managed vital strategic marketing campaigns to include print, TV, radio and seminars. Updated local and regional databases to accurately reflect current housing status, including Realtors MLS. Maintain proficient skills set and knowledge of new home sales and current financing programs. Community expert in regards to the builder, area location, community advantages, status of competition and products such as products; options, taxes, utility rates, and financing programs. Represented the builder and established balance of fairness between the welfare of the buyer, agents and the builder. Maintain weekly and monthly reports including all Monthly Performance Agreements with team. Responsible for the growth and management of team members to include interviewing and hiring of new team members. Managed all training and development of team members to support professional and personnel development. • Recipient of Ryland’s President Cup 2002
name: James Groff

title: Logistics Manager
description: TTO Lead for Logistics and Facilities task of high profile National Security Agency program. Managed team of logisticians that provided 24/7 worldwide program support coordinated and negotiated with corporate and DOD vendors to ensure full compliance of all program requirements. Worked closely with Senior Buyers, Project Managers, and Product Vendors Rep. Trained customer and company personnel at multiple sites and levels in the use of highly critical security devices. • Named finalist in Excellence in Performance Award.
name: James Groff

title: Operations Manager

Oversaw receiving department, shipping department and transportation managers to achieve company objectives and meet overall customer expectations. Evaluated overall operations and development of short and long-term goals to meet organizational objectives. Focused on the continuous improvement and enhancement of value of the service, effectiveness and profitability of operations. Negotiated with National Carriers for discounts, rebates and freight contracts. Verified deliveries and billing, enforcing all required standards and appropriate regulations were met. Ensured compliance with all company, customer and government/regulatory requirements including OSHA, ensure customer and team safety.

Monitored, processed, analyzed, and reported tasking to ensure appropriate emissions were monitored and forwarded in a timely manner.
